The architects looked in - the office also includes a kindergarten
The Avriopoint office building in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch.Design.
But who would expect a mini-children's garden here, with everything that comes with it: colorful walls, creative furniture, a lot of toys and even a mini-game on the outdoor terrace.
This Kindergarten has been available to Arch.Design employees since last year.
The design and architecture office Arch.Design, from whose studios a number of famous Br<0xC3><0xBC>nner buildings come from, calculated from the first designs for the new Avriopoint building with the premises for its company-minikindergarten.
Wisely anticipated, because most of its 90 employees (within) are in the babyboom age and the company is located in that the project brides and architects return to their workplace as soon as possible.
Along with the possibility of working shortened, the Kindergarten is another bonus that Arch.Design has to offer its employees in the concept of its social program.
The construction engineers and architects have made it so much easier to bring their demanding profession and childcare under a hat.
The Minikindergarten is an original idea of the employees of Arch.Design and with the support of the management they managed to win funding from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs for their project.
The operational kindergarten is funded by the Operational Programme Human Resources and Employment Policy from the European Social Fund and from the state budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to this financing (grants amounting to CZK 2.8 million) the necessary facilities and equipment could be procured and for the duration of 2 years is provided for qualified personnel and for the operation.
After exhausting the funds (2 years), the company Arch.Design is obliged to continue to operate the Minikindergarten for 3 more years at its own expense.
The preparation of this project took a whole year, with the company Economy Rating providing active assistance in the processing of the application.
The children are cared for by fully qualified staff - a nurse and a kindergarten teacher, the kindergarten can visit children without age restrictions, although most of them are over three years old.
And since this is a mini kindergarten, only 5 children may be present at the same time, but several children change each other over the day.
The Kindergarten operation is flexibly tailored to the needs of the parents, the children of all employees have the same rights in relation to the use of the Kindergarten - regardless of the company hierarchy and their respective position.
Although it is individual education and care, the programme content in the Mini Kindergarten is still comparable to the framework programme of pre-school education.
The children not only play here, they are mainly offered excellent lessons - from basic knowledge to pre-school lessons, in addition they also learn English.
The classroom is not only equipped with toys and creative games, but also with a computer that is available to children.
What's more - the presence of small children in the company contributes to a friendly and positive company environment.
Parents can take a look at the children at any time and so the stress of late picking up the children from a distant kindergarten is eliminated.
Therefore, parents use their working time more productively.
It is no wonder that natural and loyal employer-employee relationships also develop here.
Arch.Design thus became one of the Czech companies that offer clear benefits when applying for new employees, which are family-friendly and strengthen their personal marketing through such programs.
A bone house fascinates even after 100 years. Check out the interiors of Gaudi
The roof is like the back of a prehistoric oak, the stairs like the spine of a dinosaur and the balconies are cracked fishmowers.
This is the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> by the Catalan architect Antonio Gaudi in Barcelona.
From the local inhabitants, the house with its organic forms got the nickname "bone house".
Organic shapes, wild colors, the unusual use of stone, tile splinters and mosaics, the facades reminiscent of sheds and ubiquitous soft lines, all these are typical features of the art style of Antonio Gaudi.
The facade of the house plays with dreamy lines, delicate colors and textures reminiscent of nature and creatures.
It is only with a more precise view that it is noticed that everything is dominated by geometry, rhythm and thoughtful order.
At night, the whole fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade looks even more plastic, dramatic and the special lighting enhances the brightness of the colors even more.
The same swinging lines and swirling shapes also dominate the interior of the house.
Wave-shaped wood copies the window frames, railings, decorative elements of doors, and even gables and railings.
The house Batll<0xC3><0xB3> in the Eixample district on the busy Passeig de Gr<0xC3><0xA1>cia shopping street No. 43 was created by the reconstruction of a house from 1877, which was carried out by the architect Emilio Sala Cortese.
The reconstruction took two years and was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialist Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3>, originally consisted of the demolition of the old building and the construction of a completely new building, but ultimately he agreed to Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s idea of an unusual and also cheaper conversion.
However, the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> rental house was not designed by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> alone.
He worked with the architect Josep Maria Jujol.
Precisely on its drawing board the decorations for the representative apartment of the reality owner were created and also the use of mosaics on the facade was his idea.
However, numerous other artists and artists were also involved in the design of the facade.
The joint work on the designs for the Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> was the beginning of a fruitful collaboration between Jujola and Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Jujol was also involved in the construction of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s Casa Mil<0xC3><0xA1> house in Park G<0xC3><0xBC>ell, which also houses further works by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Shortly after its completion, the house was given by the local inhabitants of its organic forms due to the nickname "Knochenhaus".
Others, in turn, called it the special window opening mechanism because of the "walking house".
It is also said that at the very top of the building is the sword of Saint George, the patron saint of Catalonia.
But other pictorial elements also symbolize hidden religious motifs.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> designed a central heating system with ventilation ducts and typical fireplaces for the house.
Something bizarre is already motivating its 45-degree inclination.
In his creation, Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> consistently ignored all the building regulations of the time and was not in any way affected by them.
Before construction began, he obtained the appropriate building permit from the city, but the information he made about the planned reconstruction was so vague that the city fathers were so appalled at the completion of the result that they demanded help.
Among other things, the councilors were also faced with the fact that the construction with its pillars even interfered with the public civil ladder.
However, no further changes were made, quite the contrary - just fifteen days after the district's request in this regard, Josep Batll<0xC3><0xB3> submitted a request for the rental of the two highest floors of the house - and it was granted to him promptly.
The owner himself moved into the lower floors.
In the gallery on the 2nd floor there was a social lounge, on the third floor there were the bedrooms and private rooms of the apartment.
The ground floor was leased to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey building runs one step up to the roof terrace.
Due to the basic elements of the conversion, all right angles and straight lines were removed and replaced by curved and curved walls.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked with a modern concept for the mutual connection of spaces.
The social part can be fully connected by opening the salon doors, so that a larger society could speak comfortably without having to give up a certain intimacy in more confidential conversations.
The house received a rather unusual roof and two more floors thanks to Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s conversion in addition to a new fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade.
Impressive is Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s play with the light as well as the blue and white glazed tiles with which the courtyard is clad and the light courtyards.
The play of these two colors gives a maximum amount of light to all floors of the house.
In doing so, he simply took advantage of the principle that white reflects light better than dark colors that absorb sunlight on the contrary.
The Casa Batll<0xC3><0xB3> house, which was included in the UNESCO World Heritage List in 2005, can be visited by anyone today.
On the first floor, the most spacious and magnificent apartment is made accessible to the public.
The owners of the house decided only in the year on this step, on the occasion of the 150th birthday of the famous creator.
When it was found that this was a fairly affordable business, the visits were maintained, yes, they were extended to other common and the attic spaces, including the roof terrace.
However, the price for visiting the building monument is not a cardboard style, it is 16.50 euros, students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourist visas receive a 20 percent discount.
This amount exceeds the entry prices to other Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> buildings in the city.
Anyone who wants to get to know the real atmosphere of the house with its dragon towers should try to make friends with one of the homeowners and visit him at home.
The right mattress and the right bed rest? Women have different desires than men
Not the best bed frame, but the quality of the lying surface - so mattress and rust make up the good bed.
However, these must be complemented harmoniously in order to meet the wishes of the specific user.
When choosing, many things play a role - the weight, the size, the state of health and, last but not least, the sex of the sleeper.
Equally important is the interior, in which mattresses and rust have to be subordinated.
Typical example?
In a weekend home where not regularly heated, latex mattresses are not well suited, as they take much longer to "get warm".
In addition, they are much heavier than ordinary polyurethane mattresses.
And - they should be turned regularly.
After all, if they do not have enough venting ducts in the core and are still on a solid plate, moisture is present: it is not excluded that it forms under their mold.
Of course, the choice also plays a role in what you are used to.
If you have been abroad for a long time, where very high mattresses with a soft layer are common, it will be difficult to get used to a low mattress with a hard surface.
"Although all the ice hockey players who came back from the NHL have complained to me that they can't sleep right here."
"For their detachable shoulders, heels and hips, they just need a soft layer of visco foam (Memory Foam - a shape memory polymer)."
“I also recommend these to people with diabetes who suffer from a disorder of the nervous system, so that they can receive the ‘information’ from the joints and skin poorly,” explains Sylva Hadamczikov<0xC3><0xA1>, who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That’s why I took care of many ice hockey players years ago, as well as other customers these mattresses with Visco foam (Memory Foam).
"Today this is no longer a problem, because such mattresses offer, among other things, the manufacturer Tempur, the Italian company Magniflex or the Czech manufacturer Tropico."
And you don’t necessarily have to be a famous ice hockey player to learn to appreciate the benefits of Visco foam.
This "wonder" actually works quite simply.
The foam optimizes its hardness and shape according to the absorbed heat, in other words, it bends straight to the warm body.
Nowhere does it push, at night you don’t roll around like after a heavy fight.
You just sleep a lot better.
The viscoelastic foam also offers protection against decubit (wandbrand).
When choosing the mattress size, the length of the soles should still be calculated to the body size, i.e. about 21 to 34 cm.
Men and women who are 180 cm tall need a bed that is 210 to 220 cm long.
Each of the sleepers should be available at least 90 cm wide, so together 180 cm.
For single beds, for example for singles, 120 to 140 cm are attached.
The comfort for and also for any visitors.
Otherwise, the following rule applies to the ideal width of the bed: "If you are lying on your back, there should still be enough room for the slightly angled arms", advises Ing. Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>, the gymnast of the upholstery and room equipment, who has been devoting herself to the problem of healthy sleep and ergono for years.
With a double bed, everyone needs their own rust and their own mattress, but be careful when shopping so that the mattresses are equally high.
Otherwise there is nothing left but to mount the grid at different heights and this is no longer possible with every bed frame.
Foam mattresses should be at least 14 cm high, mattresses with spring skeleton 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters should be missing on the form layer and the fine pad.
“You can’t feel the feathers with your hand or when you put them on,” warns Helena Prokopov<0xC3><0xA1>.
Each mattress requires a special type of rust.
Fully upholstered beds with mattress and underlay like co-grown Siamese twins have nothing to look for in the bedroom.
These mattresses cannot be ventilated and the cover can not be washed, which is already going on today.
And since you lose between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat in a single night, it is clear that after five to seven years, the mattress slowly becomes a huge (and congested sieve).
That’s also why experts reject advertising slogans, which promise a lifetime of up to 25 years, even a lifetime warranty for mattresses.
Every thing has its when and yet.
And therefore a practical advice from the dealers: For mattresses of 120 or 140 cm width, one should not shy away from the hygiene of washable, removable covers, yet it is recommended to use a mattress saver, which can be easily removed and washed.
Even if today, as a rule, mattress covers are made with a round zipper, so that after opening you get two halves (imminently important for the washing process and the washing machine size!), the manipulation with larger mattresses, especially alone, often has to be carried out, like the unequal struggle between David and Goliath.
Do they have a solid plate in the bed instead of a rust?
Get out of here!
Or at most for a bed for unloved guests and for a single night.
Also, they should prefer to use the plate with ventilation holes (if they are not already inside) and mattresses with spring skeleton and 15 cm minimum height with so-called pocket spring cores and fine padding.
Polyurethane mattresses do not belong on such a substrate.
For non-adjustable lattice grids with 14 to 18 spring strips (lames) are suitable latex or sandwich mattresses (if applicable also combinations of latex and coconut), always pay for grids with a larger number of lattice, i.e. of 28 or more spring strips, with Lordos support in the lumbar vertebral area, and the possibility of regulating the lattice and lattice.
Adjustable slats do not include mattresses with spring skeleton, as they do not respond to the ergonomic adjustment.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the spring strips, special flexible shoulder modules are also offered.
This involves a special fastening of the spring strips, which allows the spring strips to be pressed in or even angled in such a way that they allow for the punctual lowering of the shoulder of the sleeper.
Especially for men with wide shoulders an important thing.
There are even mattress manufacturers who have started using soft zones for the shoulder area in "men's mattresses".
It is also intended for the ladies - they are given these soft zones in the hip area.
For the most demanding customers, point-elastic wing spring systems (lattoflex) or rust with point-elastic contact pads with so-called multitortion spring are designed.
The pressure is distributed over several points, thereby reducing the voltage.
But - if you use a bad (too big and full) pillow for the right mattress and the right rust, most of the benefits are lost again.
Here too, a rule of thumb: the pillow should support the head, its tips should only reach to the shoulders so that the shoulder muscles can relax.
Ideally, therefore, a 50 x 60 cm pillow appears, as the Scandinavians like it.
In the side position, the head cushion (along with the shoulder relief zone in the rust or soft zone in the mattress) should balance the shoulder height.
Our modern mattresses have something in common with the old (heavy) straw bags.
Modern manufacturers are increasingly using natural materials or at least their blends.
In the case of mattresses, the new magic word is "Bio".
Instead of petroleum raw materials, more and more natural oils are used to produce polyurethane foams - for example, castor oil and soya oil.
Soy is probably used by all well-known manufacturers.
“Bio is the name given to mattresses, which consists of their core materials of purely natural origin,” explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek from Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used in the manufacture of mattress covers - one of the first was Aloe Vera.
However, you can also indulge in microcapsules that spread fresh forest or lavender scent when you sleep.
There is also a difference between a man and a woman.
While in men a "cooler" plant extract from birch leaves is used, so that the mattress cover can absorb the heat and cool the body, the covers for women have "warming" effect.
Extracts from red paprika extracts stimulate blood circulation, so the weaker sex becomes quite warm when sleeping.
And today's favorites?
Mattresses made of cold foam (it has larger pores with destroyed cell structure and is therefore more breathable than commercial polyurethane and also much more flexible).
